{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place coriander seeds and cumin seeds into mixing bowl and toast <b>10 min\/Varoma\/speed 2<b>, <strong>without measuring cup<\/strong>.","Add ginger, oil, garlic and lemongrass and chop <b>10 sec\/speed 10<b>.","Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula and chop <b>10 sec\/speed 10<b>.","Add ground turmeric, salt, sugar, fish sauce and coconut milk and mix <b>5 sec\/speed 3<b>. Transfer marinade into a bowl.","Place bowl with marinade onto mixing bowl lid and weigh pork into it. Stir well to coat, then cover with plastic wrap and place into refrigerator for a minimum of 6 hours or overnight.","Soak 12 wooden skewers in a bowl of warm water for 30 minutes. Preheat grill and line a large baking tray (30 x 40 cm) with aluminium foil and set aside.","Thread marinated pork onto skewers (approx. 3 pieces per skewer) and place onto prepared tray. Grill for 18-25 minutes, turning occasionally, or until pork is cooked through, then serve."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["¼ tsp coriander seeds","¼ tsp cumin seeds","2 cm piece fresh ginger, peeled and cut into thin, round slices (2 mm)","20 g olive oil","4 garlic cloves","½ stalk fresh lemongrass, tough outer layer removed, cut into pieces (2 cm)","½ tsp ground turmeric","1 tsp salt","1 tbsp white sugar","20 g fish sauce","100 g coconut milk","680 g pork fillet, cut into large pieces (3-4 cm) (see Tips)","warm water, for soaking"]}],"id":"r142940","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-GcmHtBxNdcs\/XZMvlJMYaiI\/AAAAAAAAaTs\/4e-87ksfaxUQTP2jq-C-560RSR_mKRxtACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_jwHL9vhkSx_Q-asw.png","title":"Thai-style grilled pork skewers","publishedAt":"2017-08-20T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"13.4 g","fat":"3.6 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"1.7 g","calories":"391 kJ \/ 93 kcal"},"usefulItems":"bowl, plastic wrap, large bowl, wooden skewers, baking tray (30 x 40 cm), aluminium foil, refrigerator, oven grill","hintsAndTricks":["You can use either pork fillet or diced pork shoulder in this recipe."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","7h 25m","12 portions"]}